  "schema_version": "GOLD_ENGINE_COMMANDS_FULL_V1_4_15",
  "description": "Gold v1.4.15. Implements GOLD_PIPELINE_SPEC_V3_TASK_RELEVANCE.md Section 3 (the Detector safety-net flag + Scorer hard ceiling), the one remaining open item from V3/V5. New: det_vip_v18d_3_topic_alignment_risk.py (was det_vip_v18d_2.py) adds detect_topic_alignment_risk() -- a cheap CHEAP_MODEL call comparing essay content against the assigned prompt, independent of the Evaluator's own (already-fixed, v8.4) relevance judgment -- and surfaces it as a new top-level 'topic_alignment_risk' field on every per-essay detector result. New: det_vip_cli_bridge_v1_1.py (was det_vip_cli_bridge_v1.py) imports the new detector module; no other behavior change, the new field passes through as a native det_vip key already. Confirmed via direct code read that scorer_input_evidence_guard_standalone_v1_4_7.py's enrich_detector() (copy.deepcopy(detector) at its core) and evaluator_rubric_bridge_v1.py's apply_to_record() (mutates the same record objects in place, writes back the full detector_for_scorer) both already pass the new field through to the scorer's actual input with zero changes needed to either file. New: detector_to_errormap_v3_1_standalone.py (was detector_to_errormap_v3_standalone.py) explicitly extracts topic_alignment_risk and adds it as a new top-level field on the errormap artifact -- build_errormap() builds its return value from scratch rather than passing the input through, so this one *did* need an explicit change -- making the flag visible to Priority Engine, Directive, and Feedback Report via the same {errormap} path every other Detector signal already takes, per the spec's requirement for a visible student-facing warning, not just a silently adjusted score. New: premium_unified_scorer_v1_4_2_topic_ceiling.py (was premium_unified_scorer_v1_4_1_fixed.py) applies the hard ceiling itself: if topic_alignment_risk.risk_flag is true with confidence >= 0.55 (config: topic_alignment_risk_confidence_min), task_response is capped at band 3 (config: topic_alignment_risk_task_response_cap) and overall_band is recomputed accordingly. This is applied as an unconditional post-processing step after apply_tier_governor(), deliberately NOT wired into the existing task_schema_status/true_fail/resolve_task_status() machinery -- that machinery's high_review/clean6/soft55 rescue heuristics exist to protect against a different failure mode (false-positive structural coverage fails on otherwise-strong essays) and would otherwise rescue exactly the well-written-but-off-topic case this ceiling exists to catch, undermining 'regardless of the Evaluator's own judgment' per the spec. Verified locally with a synthetic record: an essay that would otherwise score task_response=7/overall=6.5 is correctly capped to task_response=3/overall=5.5 when the flag fires at confidence 0.88; a risk_flag=False signal and a below-threshold-confidence signal (0.4) both correctly leave the score untouched (fail-safe); no signal at all is bit-for-bit identical to the v1.4.14 behavior (no regression). Full Gold v1.4.14 command config carried forward unchanged otherwise.",
